title: H1_PO755IR01: Pancreatic islet sample from organ donor
source_name_ch1: Pancreatic islet sample from cultured islets
characteristics_ch1: age (years): 76 | gender (m/f): M | body mass index (bmi): 24.49 | icu (intensive care unit) glycemia (mmol/l): 15.4 | diabetes status (nd (non-diabetic), t2d (type 2 diabetic)): T2D | batch: 1
extract_protocol_ch1: Groups of 100-120 islets were hand-picked, rinsed in sterile PBS (Sigma-Aldrich) and centrifuged at 3,000 x g for 5 min; the supernatant was disposed and 100 μl of extraction buffer (PicoPure RNA Isolation Kit, Life Technologies, Foster City, California) was added. Samples were incubated at 42 °C for 30 min, centrifuged at 3,000 x g for 2 min, and the supernatant collected and stored at -80°C until the isolation procedure. RNA isolation was performed according to the protocol provided by the manufacturer. Briefly, 100 μl of 70% ethanol were added to the cell extract, the mixture was added to the purification columns, washed and DNase treatment performed by incubation with 40 μl of DNase I solution (RNase-Free DNase Set, Qiagen GmbH, Hilden, Germany) for 15 min. Two additional washing steps were performed and RNA was eluted in 30 μl of elution buffer. RNA concentration and purity were evaluated using NanoDrop 2000c spectrophotometer (Thermo Scientific, Wilmington, DE); quality was evaluated using the Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer system and the Agilent RNA 6000 Pico Kit (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: 10 - 25 ng total RNA was amplified using the Ovation RNA Amplification System V2 and subsequently labelled with Biotin using the Encore™ Biotin Module following the manufacturer's instructions (NuGEN Technologies, San Carlos, CA, USA).
hyb_protocol: 3.75µg cDNA per sample were hybridized to Affymetrix HG-U133 Plus 2.0 GeneChips (Affymetrix) for 16-18 hours at 45°C and 60 rpm in a rotating hybridization oven (Hybridization Oven 640, Affymetrix). The array was subsequently washed and stained with a fluidics station (GeneChip® Fluidics Station 450, Affymetrix) following the EukGe_WSv4_450 fluidics protocol for eukaryotic 3´-expression arrays.
scan_protocol: Arrays were scanned using GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G (Affymetrix).
data_processing: Empirical Bayes moderated t statistics and corresponding p-values were computed using the Limma package in R correcting for age and sex covariates. P values were adjusted for multiple comparisons using the Benjamini Hochberg procedure.

characteristics_ch1: age (years): 72 | gender (m/f): M | body mass index (bmi): 24.22 | icu (intensive care unit) glycemia (mmol/l): 23.3 | diabetes status (nd (non-diabetic), t2d (type 2 diabetic)): T2D | batch: 3
extract_protocol_ch1: Groups of 100-120 islets were hand-picked, rinsed in sterile PBS (Sigma-Aldrich) and centrifuged at 3,000 x g for 5 min; the supernatant was disposed and 100 μl of extraction buffer (PicoPure RNA Isolation Kit, Life Technologies, Foster City, California) was added. Samples were incubated at 42 °C for 30 min, centrifuged at 3,000 x g for 2 min, and the supernatant collected and stored at -80°C until the isolation procedure. RNA isolation was performed according to the protocol provided by the manufacturer. Briefly, 100 μl of 70% ethanol were added to the cell extract, the mixture was added to the purification columns, washed and DNase treatment performed by incubation with 40 μl of DNase I solution (RNase-Free DNase Set, Qiagen GmbH, Hilden, Germany) for 15 min. Two additional washing steps were performed and RNA was eluted in 30 μl of elution buffer. RNA concentration and purity were evaluated using NanoDrop 2000c spectrophotometer (Thermo Scientific, Wilmington, DE); quality was evaluated using the Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer system and the Agilent RNA 6000 Pico Kit (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: 10 - 25 ng total RNA was amplified using the Ovation RNA Amplification System V2 and subsequently labelled with Biotin using the Encore™ Biotin Module following the manufacturer's instructions (NuGEN Technologies, San Carlos, CA, USA).
hyb_protocol: 3.75µg cDNA per sample were hybridized to Affymetrix HG-U133 Plus 2.0 GeneChips (Affymetrix) for 16-18 hours at 45°C and 60 rpm in a rotating hybridization oven (Hybridization Oven 640, Affymetrix). The array was subsequently washed and stained with a fluidics station (GeneChip® Fluidics Station 450, Affymetrix) following the EukGe_WSv4_450 fluidics protocol for eukaryotic 3´-expression arrays.
scan_protocol: Arrays were scanned using GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G (Affymetrix).
data_processing: Empirical Bayes moderated t statistics and corresponding p-values were computed using the Limma package in R correcting for age and sex covariates. P values were adjusted for multiple comparisons using the Benjamini Hochberg procedure.

characteristics_ch1: age (years): 85 | gender (m/f): M | body mass index (bmi): 25.47 | icu (intensive care unit) glycemia (mmol/l): 8.6 | diabetes status (nd (non-diabetic), t2d (type 2 diabetic)): ND | batch: 5
extract_protocol_ch1: Groups of 100-120 islets were hand-picked, rinsed in sterile PBS (Sigma-Aldrich) and centrifuged at 3,000 x g for 5 min; the supernatant was disposed and 100 μl of extraction buffer (PicoPure RNA Isolation Kit, Life Technologies, Foster City, California) was added. Samples were incubated at 42 °C for 30 min, centrifuged at 3,000 x g for 2 min, and the supernatant collected and stored at -80°C until the isolation procedure. RNA isolation was performed according to the protocol provided by the manufacturer. Briefly, 100 μl of 70% ethanol were added to the cell extract, the mixture was added to the purification columns, washed and DNase treatment performed by incubation with 40 μl of DNase I solution (RNase-Free DNase Set, Qiagen GmbH, Hilden, Germany) for 15 min. Two additional washing steps were performed and RNA was eluted in 30 μl of elution buffer. RNA concentration and purity were evaluated using NanoDrop 2000c spectrophotometer (Thermo Scientific, Wilmington, DE); quality was evaluated using the Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer system and the Agilent RNA 6000 Pico Kit (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: 10 - 25 ng total RNA was amplified using the Ovation RNA Amplification System V2 and subsequently labelled with Biotin using the Encore™ Biotin Module following the manufacturer's instructions (NuGEN Technologies, San Carlos, CA, USA).
hyb_protocol: 3.75µg cDNA per sample were hybridized to Affymetrix HG-U133 Plus 2.0 GeneChips (Affymetrix) for 16-18 hours at 45°C and 60 rpm in a rotating hybridization oven (Hybridization Oven 640, Affymetrix). The array was subsequently washed and stained with a fluidics station (GeneChip® Fluidics Station 450, Affymetrix) following the EukGe_WSv4_450 fluidics protocol for eukaryotic 3´-expression arrays.
scan_protocol: Arrays were scanned using GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G (Affymetrix).
data_processing: Empirical Bayes moderated t statistics and corresponding p-values were computed using the Limma package in R correcting for age and sex covariates. P values were adjusted for multiple comparisons using the Benjamini Hochberg procedure.

Samples were incubated at 42 °C for 30 min, centrifuged at 3,000 x g for 2 min, and the supernatant collected and stored at -80°C until the isolation procedure. RNA isolation was performed according to the protocol provided by the manufacturer. Briefly, 100 μl of 70% ethanol were added to the cell extract, the mixture was added to the purification columns, washed and DNase treatment performed by incubation with 40 μl of DNase I solution (RNase-Free DNase Set, Qiagen GmbH, Hilden, Germany) for 15 min. Two additional washing steps were performed and RNA was eluted in 30 μl of elution buffer. RNA concentration and purity were evaluated using NanoDrop 2000c spectrophotometer (Thermo Scientific, Wilmington, DE); quality was evaluated using the Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer system and the Agilent RNA 6000 Pico Kit (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: 10 - 25 ng total RNA was amplified using the Ovation RNA Amplification System V2 and subsequently labelled with Biotin using the Encore™ Biotin Module following the manufacturer's instructions (NuGEN Technologies, San Carlos, CA, USA).
hyb_protocol: 3.75µg cDNA per sample were hybridized to Affymetrix HG-U133 Plus 2.0 GeneChips (Affymetrix) for 16-18 hours at 45°C and 60 rpm in a rotating hybridization oven (Hybridization Oven 640, Affymetrix). The array was subsequently washed and stained with a fluidics station (GeneChip® Fluidics Station 450, Affymetrix) following the EukGe_WSv4_450 fluidics protocol for eukaryotic 3´-expression arrays.
scan_protocol: Arrays were scanned using GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G (Affymetrix).
data_processing: Empirical Bayes moderated t statistics and corresponding p-values were computed using the Limma package in R correcting for age and sex covariates. P values were adjusted for multiple comparisons using the Benjamini Hochberg procedure.
